-- Aeon First-Quarter Profit Rises on Supermarket Cost Cuts, Nikkei Reports
-- Fergus Maguire
-- 2010-07-05T21:05:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/aeon-first-quarter-profit-rises-on-supermarket-cost-cuts-nikkei-reports.html

          
          
             Aeon Co. may post first-quarter
operating profit of about 22 billion yen, up 150 percent from a
year earlier, on cost cuts at its supermarkets, Nikkei English
News said, without citing anyone.  
 Sales in the March-May period are likely to have fallen 3
percent to about 1.21 trillion yen.  The retailer is likely to
post net income of 2.4 billion yen, from a year earlier loss,
the report said.  
          
          


  


        